  ,   McComish  .","Americanized form of Danish, Norwegian, and North German   Thomsen  . Compare   Thompson  ."]},{"name":"Thom","meanings":["Scottish and English: from the Middle English personal name <i>T(h)om(me)</i>, a pet form of   Thomas  . In Scotland, <i>Thom</i> is also an Anglicized form of Gaelic <i>Mac Thom</i>, see   McComb  .","German: from the personal name <i>Thom</i>, a pet form of   Thomas  . This surname is also found in France.","Chinese: variant Romanization of the surname 譚, see   Tan   1."]},{"name":"Tomson","meanings":["English: variant of   Thompson  ."]},{"name":"Thompsom","meanings":["Altered form of   Thompson  ."]},{"name":"Tompson","meanings":["English: variant of   Thompson  ."]}]},{"name":"Christian","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From Latin <i>Christianus</i> ‘follower of Christ’, in use as a given name from the Middle Ages onwards, especially as a girl's name. The name of <i>Christ</i> (Greek <i>Khristos</i>) is a translation of the Hebrew term <i>Messiah</i> ‘anointed’."],"variants":[{"name":"Christianne","meanings":["From Latin <i>Christianus</i> ‘follower of Christ’, in use as a given name from the Middle Ages onwards, especially as a girl's name. The name of <i>Christ</i> (Greek <i>Khristos</i>) is a translation of the Hebrew term <i>Messiah</i> ‘anointed’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Christian Thompson was born about 1380, in Scotland. She married Angus MacPhee of Glen Spean before 1395, in Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. She died in Inverness-shire, Scotland, United Kingdom."},"et":{"about 1380–":"umbes 1380–Surnud","1380–1439":"1380–1439","1395–1472":"1395–1472","1380–Female":"1380–Surnud","about 1380":"umbes 1380","before 1395":"enne 1395","1395":"1395","1472":"1472","1380":"1380","1439":"1439","Lochaber, Inverness-shire, Scotland":"Lochaber, Inverness-shire, Scotland","Inverness-shire, Scotland":"Inverness-shire, Šot